It is a beautiful Valentines today in New York so I picked you all some Morning Glories in the AM light.  It’s all there on the sidewalk.  The mixed emotions, the missed connection, the day dreamer, the three graces in procession, the over achiever, the just getting by . . . Wanted to give you a dozen but all you are getting is 10 . . . just like the bouquets at the Bodega. @dirtywhitebucks @goldteethandco

Join us Thursday August 17th 5-8pm!

Leica Store San Francisco is excited to announce the relaunch of our gallery program with Lonely Car Company, an exhibition of photographs by New York-based artist Gus Powell @dirtywhitebucks . Spanning Powell's career, this exhibition features over 30 works made in the past 20 years covering three of Powell’s most important projects, The Lonely Ones, Family Car Trouble, and The Company of Strangers.

Please RSVP for the reception and book signing with the artist via the link in bio.

Images:
Gus Powell, Waiting, from the series Family Car Trouble (2018).
Gus Powell, Our Secret, from the series Lunch Pictures (1999-2007).
Gus Powell, Yes., from the series The Lonely Ones (2015).

The Gallery at Leica Store San Francisco is excited to now have on view, "Lonely Car Company," an exhibition of photographs by New York-based artist Gus Powell @dirtywhitebucks . Spanning Powell's career, this exhibition features over 30 works made in the past 20 years covering three of Powell’s most important projects, The Lonely Ones, Family Car Trouble, and The Company of Strangers.

We hope to see you this Thursday (8/17), for the artist reception and book signing between 5-8pm. For those of you who aren't in town or able to visit, stay tuned as we will be sharing a gallery walk through video with Gus at a future date!

Lonely Car Co. Opening at Leica SF!

We are delighted to announce an exclusive workshop aimed at enhancing your photography skills and broadening your creative horizons with photographer Gus Powell @dirtywhitebucks , whose photographs are currently on view in our gallery. The workshop, which will take place 9/30 - 10/1 is titled "Based On A True Story" and is designed for individuals who aspire to explore the narrative and artistic possibilities of photography. 

Workshop highlights include:

Deep Dive into Gus Powell's Artist Practice: Understand the inspiration, creation, and execution behind Powell's renowned projects, editorial commissions, and street photography.

Portfolio Reviews: Receive personalized feedback on your existing work to identify areas for improvement and refinement.

Hands-on Exercises: Engage in practical exercises focusing on storytelling and sequencing, vital aspects of narrative photography.

Classroom Editing Assignments: Collaborate on editing tasks that marry text, image, and design, leaving you with a completed project by the end of the workshop.

Participation is subject to an application (no fee) process. To be considered, we request that you submit a statement of your intent along with a selection of images. Workshop max - 12 participants. We encourage you to submit your application at your earliest convenience.

🔴 More details at the workshop link in bio!
